  Prerequirities
-------------------------

This application is just test app.

You need mysql (see your distribution how to install MySQL.

Debian distro:

You can install debian package from http://www.volf.eu/debian/pool/main/libmojolicious-perl_3.11-1_all.deb)

You can install other packages from debian also

 libdbi-perl, libdbd-pg-perl, libdbd-mysql-perl, libintl-perl, libmojolicious-perl, libdatetime-locale-perl, libdatetime-perl, libdatetime-timezone-perl, libvalidation-class-perl

Non debian way:

To install mojolicious from CPAN see http://mojolicio.us/ documentation

You can install modules from CPAN

  DateTime;
  DBD::Pg
  DBD::mysql
  DBI;
  Encode;
  File::Basename
  File::Spec::Functions
  Locale::Messages
  POSIX
  Scalar::Util
  Test::More


  Download sources
-------------------------

git://github.com/norbertvolf/treemanager.git


  Create database
-------------------------

Create database and put script/sql/rev0001.sql to database
Then setup database in tree_manager.conf 

  Run application
-------------------------

You can use mojolicious startes example morbo scripts/tree_manager and http://localhost:3000/tree in your browser

